parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat frame can cause the seat to wobble or collapse, leading to a loss of control of the vehicle, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat feels loose or wobbly
the seat collapses or dips to one side
the seat moves unexpectedly while driving
the seat is difficult to adjust or returns to its original position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause a distraction to the driver, block their view of the road, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The sun visor falls down or will not stay in the up position
blocking the driver's view
and causing a distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power, stalling, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery and brake warning lights come on
the vehicle loses power
stalls
or has difficulty starting
the alternator voltage is low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or have difficulty starting, which can increase the risk of accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery and brake warning lights come on
the vehicle loses power
stalls
or has difficulty starting
the airbag light flashes on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door locks can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to safety issues if the doors are unlocked while driving.
symptoms: The doors do not lock or unlock using the remote control or buttons
the doors only lock or unlock manually.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light flashes on and off
the airbag system is not functioning properly.
